TITLE: Defining Story Pools with ProvinceStory in PHP
DESCRIPTION: This code defines a ProvinceStory class extending Zenstruck\Foundry\Story to create and manage pools of Province objects using ProvinceFactory. It demonstrates adding multiple provinces to a pool, as well as adding a single object to both a pool and a specific state.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstruck/foundry/blob/2.x/docs/index.rst#_snippet_77

LANGUAGE: PHP
CODE:
```
// src/Story/ProvinceStory.php
namespace App\Story;

use App\Factory\ProvinceFactory;
use Zenstruck\Foundry\Story;

final class ProvinceStory extends Story
{
    public function build(): void
    {
        // add collection to a "pool"
        $this->addToPool('be', ProvinceFactory::createMany(5, ['country' => 'BE']));

        // equivalent to above
        $this->addToPool('be', ProvinceFactory::new(['country' => 'BE'])->many(5));

        // add single object to a pool
        $this->addToPool('be', ProvinceFactory::createOne(['country' => 'BE']));

        // add single object to single pool and make available as "state"
        $this->addState('be-1', ProvinceFactory::createOne(['country' => 'BE']), 'be');
    }
}
```

