TITLE: Defining Factory States for PostFactory (PHP)
DESCRIPTION: Shows how to define custom states within a factory to create objects with specific characteristics. These states can be chained to create complex object configurations, improving test readability and maintainability. States are methods returning `$this->with([...])`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstruck/foundry/blob/2.x/docs/index.rst#_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: php
CODE:
```
final class PostFactory extends PersistentProxyObjectFactory
{
    // ...

    public function published(): self
    {
        // call setPublishedAt() and pass a random DateTime
        return $this->with(['published_at' => self::faker()->dateTime()]);
    }

    public function unpublished(): self
    {
        return $this->with(['published_at' => null]);
    }

    public function withViewCount(?int $count = null): self
    {
        return $this->with(function () use ($count) {
            return ['view_count' => $count ?? self::faker()->numberBetween(0, 10000)];
        });
    }
}
```

