TITLE: YAML Configuration for Database Resetting with Migrations
DESCRIPTION: Configures Zenstruck Foundry to reset the database using Doctrine migrations. This allows for a more controlled database setup during testing. Optionally, it allows passing configurations to the doctrine:migrations:migrate command.
SOURCE: https://github.com/zenstruck/foundry/blob/2.x/docs/index.rst#_snippet_46

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
# config/packages/zenstruck_foundry.yaml
when@dev: # see Bundle Configuration section about sharing this in the test environment
    zenstruck_foundry:
        orm:
            reset:
                mode: migrate # enables resetting with migrations

                # optional: allows you to pass additional configuration to the doctrine:migrations:migrate command
                migrations:
                    configurations:
                        - '%kernel.root_dir%/migrations/configuration.php'
                        - 'migrations/configuration.yaml'
```

